"{\"uid\": \"dailyhive.com-vancouver-vancouver-olympic-village-elementary-school-funding-update\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Urbanized  van  No capital funding for the construction of thelong-envisioned new Olympic Village elementary schoolwas included in the2024 provincial budget announced today.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 173, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But when asked during a closed session for media, BC Minister of Finance Katrine Conway quipped that an announcement would be forthcoming in the \\\"coming weeks.\\\"\", \"from\": 175, \"to\": 335, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 225, \"end\": 227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Columbia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.021791780059576e-20, \"text\": \"BC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Columbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Columbia\"}, {\"begin\": 256, \"end\": 262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conwy\", \"score\": 0.9920695298827724, \"rank\": 0.007993865226725313, \"text\": \"Conway\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conwy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conwy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An elementary school serving the growing high-density residential neighbourhood in Vancouver's Southeast False Creek area has been planned by the municipal government since the 2000s.\", \"from\": 337, \"to\": 520, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 420, \"end\": 429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2996484119493963e-16, \"text\": \"Vancouver\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In more recent years,municipal officials, residents in the area, andparents of nearby schools experiencing long waitlists at their at-capacity catchment schoolhave been calling for the provincial government to expedite funding for the project.\", \"from\": 521, \"to\": 764, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The BC NDP included an Olympic Village elementary school as acampaign promise in the 2020 election, and the last formal update provided on the project was inJune 2022, when the BC Ministry of Education and Child Care provided the concept plan with preliminary approval, enabling Vancouver School Board to enter the next stage of planning.\", \"from\": 766, \"to\": 1104, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 770, \"end\": 776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Columbia_New_Democratic_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"BC NDP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Columbia_New_Democratic_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Columbia_New_Democratic_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 789, \"end\": 804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 0.9999999886690604, \"rank\": 1.1330750225352747e-08, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}, {\"begin\": 1045, \"end\": 1054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2996484119493963e-16, \"text\": \"Vancouver\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\"}, {\"begin\": 1045, \"end\": 1067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver_School_Board\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Vancouver School Board\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver_School_Board\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver_School_Board\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A forthcoming funding announcement for this project also comes ahead of the general provincial election later in 2024.\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In accordance with the City of Vancouver's Southeast False Creek Plan, the new school will be located on a temporary open grassy parcel on the east side of Hinge Park - the parcel at the southwest corner of the intersection of Athletes Way and Columbia Street, next to the seawall.\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1507, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2021, VSB and Vancouver City Council approved a 99-year lease for the use of the City-owned site for an elementary school.\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1526, \"end\": 1535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2996484119493963e-16, \"text\": \"Vancouver\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\"}, {\"begin\": 1526, \"end\": 1548, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver_City_Council\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Vancouver City Council\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver_City_Council\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver_City_Council\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Vancouver City Council and the Vancouver School Board (VSB) announced today they have approved entering into a 99-year lease for the school site.\", \"from\": 1636, \"to\": 1781, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1636, \"end\": 1658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver_City_Council\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Vancouver City Council\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver_City_Council\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver_City_Council\"}, {\"begin\": 1636, \"end\": 1645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2996484119493963e-16, \"text\": \"Vancouver\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\"}, {\"begin\": 1667, \"end\": 1689, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver_School_Board\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Vancouver School Board\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver_School_Board\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver_School_Board\"}, {\"begin\": 1667, \"end\": 1676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2996484119493963e-16, \"text\": \"Vancouver\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Master plan of Southeast False Creek, which includes the Olympic Village.\", \"from\": 1783, \"to\": 1856, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1840, \"end\": 1855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 0.9999999886690604, \"rank\": 1.1330750225352747e-08, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The location of the planned elementary school at Hinge Park is circled in red.\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1935, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(City of Vancouver/Daily Hive)  Site of the future Olympic Village elementary school.\", \"from\": 1936, \"to\": 2021, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(City of Vancouver)  The large open grassy site at Hinge Park in Vancouver's Olympic Village is slated to become an elementary school and daycare.\", \"from\": 2022, \"to\": 2168, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2087, \"end\": 2096, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2996484119493963e-16, \"text\": \"Vancouver\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\"}, {\"begin\": 2099, \"end\": 2114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 0.9999999886690604, \"rank\": 1.1330750225352747e-08, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Kenneth Chan/Daily Hive)  Based on a previous VSB facilities plan, this Kindergarten to Grade 7 school could have a capacity for over 500 students and incorporate a childcare facility, with an elementary school and childcare facility co-location increasingly common for new build projects.\", \"from\": 2169, \"to\": 2459, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2170, \"end\": 2182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenneth_Chan_Kai-tai\", \"score\": 0.8253855353336108, \"rank\": 0.21155503360740105, \"text\": \"Kenneth Chan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenneth_Chan_Kai-tai\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenneth_Chan_Kai-tai\"}, {\"begin\": 2183, \"end\": 2193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Hive\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daily Hive\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Hive\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Hive\"}, {\"begin\": 2242, \"end\": 2254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kindergarten\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.7517414288154483e-12, \"text\": \"Kindergarten\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kindergarten\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kindergarten\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Conway also faced questions about the provincial government's urgency to respond to the City of Surrey and Surrey School District's (SSD) pleas to direct more capital funding to ramp up the pace of building new permanent purpose-built structures toreplace Surrey's growing dependency on portable structures- including thefuture possibility of two-storey portable structures- and the community's continued high enrolment due to high population growth.\", \"from\": 2461, \"to\": 2911, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2461, \"end\": 2467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conwy\", \"score\": 0.9920695298827724, \"rank\": 0.007993865226725313, \"text\": \"Conway\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conwy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conwy\"}, {\"begin\": 2717, \"end\": 2723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surrey\", \"score\": 0.9999999939982445, \"rank\": 4.2428076433838896e-09, \"text\": \"Surrey\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surrey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surrey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the new school year starting in September 2024, there could bealmost 400 portables at public schools across Surrey.\", \"from\": 2913, \"to\": 3031, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3024, \"end\": 3030, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surrey\", \"score\": 0.9999999939982445, \"rank\": 4.2428076433838896e-09, \"text\": \"Surrey\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surrey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surrey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As of 2019, about 10% of SSD's students were already in portables.\", \"from\": 3032, \"to\": 3098, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3057, \"end\": 3060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Solid-state_drive\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.7549661892096174e-30, \"text\": \"SSD\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Solid-state_drive\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Solid-state_drive\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Coincidentally, today, SSD announced it will resort to extending the school day at five of its most crowded secondary schools to address capacity challenges, including at Grandview Heights Secondary, Fleetwood Park Secondary, Lord Tweedsmuir Secondary, Kwantlen Park Secondary, and Tamanawis Secondary.\", \"from\": 3100, \"to\": 3402, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3123, \"end\": 3126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Solid-state_drive\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.7549661892096174e-30, \"text\": \"SSD\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Solid-state_drive\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Solid-state_drive\"}, {\"begin\": 3326, \"end\": 3351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lord_Tweedsmuir_Secondary_School\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lord Tweedsmuir Secondary\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3914\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lord_Tweedsmuir_Secondary_School\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lord_Tweedsmuir_Secondary_School\"}, {\"begin\": 3353, \"end\": 3361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kwantlen_Polytechnic_University\", \"score\": 0.9999999316701201, \"rank\": 6.833000981933131e-08, \"text\": \"Kwantlen\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kwantlen_Polytechnic_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kwantlen_Polytechnic_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This will start in September 2024.\", \"from\": 3403, \"to\": 3437, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"An extended school day will enable a staggered student attendance schedule to increase each school's capacity by 10% to 15%.\", \"from\": 3439, \"to\": 3563, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This extended school day involves lengthening the school day by one block/class period, so there will be five blocks instead of four blocks.\", \"from\": 3564, \"to\": 3704, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By May 2024, SSD will decide on whether it will deploy the same extended school day strategy at Fraser Heights Secondary and Salish Secondary.\", \"from\": 3706, \"to\": 3848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3719, \"end\": 3722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Solid-state_drive\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.7549661892096174e-30, \"text\": \"SSD\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Solid-state_drive\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Solid-state_drive\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Extended day is not an option we want to implement.\", \"from\": 3850, \"to\": 3902, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We know there are likely going to be challenges for our staff, our students, and their families.\", \"from\": 3903, \"to\": 3999, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Our preference is to construct new schools and additions in neighbourhoods where they are needed, but we have to explore other options while we continue to advocate for provincial funding,\\\" said Laurie Larsen, chair of the SSD, in a statement.\", \"from\": 4000, \"to\": 4243, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4223, \"end\": 4226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Solid-state_drive\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.7549661892096174e-30, \"text\": \"SSD\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Solid-state_drive\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Solid-state_drive\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are at a point now where it's very difficult for us to accommodate any additional student enrolment growth in the existing infrastructure we have, particularly at our secondary schools where the majority of our schools are significantly over capacity.\\\"\", \"from\": 4245, \"to\": 4501, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Portable structures at North Surrey Secondary School.\", \"from\": 4503, \"to\": 4556, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4526, \"end\": 4555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Surrey_Secondary_School\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"North Surrey Secondary School\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3914\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Surrey_Secondary_School\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Surrey_Secondary_School\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Google Maps)  By signing up, you agree to receive email newsletters from Daily Hive.\", \"from\": 4557, \"to\": 4642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4631, \"end\": 4641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Hive\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daily Hive\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Hive\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Hive\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You can unsubscribe at any time by clicking \\\"unsubscribe\\\" at the bottom of the email.\", \"from\": 4644, \"to\": 4729, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Daily Hive is a division of ZoomerMedia Limited, 70 Jefferson Avenue, Toronto ON M6K 3H4.\", \"from\": 4731, \"to\": 4820, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4731, \"end\": 4741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Hive\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daily Hive\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Hive\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Hive\"}, {\"begin\": 4759, \"end\": 4770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ZoomerMedia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ZoomerMedia\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ZoomerMedia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ZoomerMedia\"}, {\"begin\": 4801, \"end\": 4808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toronto\", \"score\": 0.9999999999913598, \"rank\": 8.56530009548281e-12, \"text\": \"Toronto\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toronto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toronto\"}, {\"begin\": 4809, \"end\": 4811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ontario\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.460865442717389e-23, \"text\": \"ON\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ontario\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ontario\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"National  News  Urbanized  Food & Drink  Sports  Events  Lifestyle  Travel  Business & Tech  National  News  Urbanized  Food & Drink  Sports  Events  Lifestyle  Travel  Business & Tech  Daily Hive is a Canadian-born online news source, established in 2008, that creates compelling, hyperlocal content.Part of\", \"from\": 4822, \"to\": 5130, \"entities\": []}]}"